   "source": [
    "# Complex projective coordinates on surface of genus two\n",
    "\n",
    "We use complex projective coordinate to parametrize the two-dimensional void of a surface of genus two."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from dreimac import GeometryExamples, PlotUtils, ComplexProjectiveCoords, ProjectiveMapUtils, GeometryUtils"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

      ],
      "text/plain": [
       "Canvas(toolbar=Toolbar(toolitems=[('Home', 'Reset original view', 'home', 'home'), ('Back', 'Back to previous …"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "X = GeometryExamples.genus_two_surface()\n",
    "\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(4,4))\n",
    "ax = fig.add_subplot(projection=\"3d\")\n",
    "ax.scatter(X[:,0], X[:,1], X[:,2], s=0.1)\n",
    "PlotUtils.set_axes_equal(ax) ; plt.axis(\"off\") ; fig.subplots_adjust(top=1, bottom=0, left=0, right=1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "dist_mat, pointcloud_permutation = GeometryUtils.landmark_geodesic_distance(X, 400, 10)\n",
    "cpc = ComplexProjectiveCoords(dist_mat, n_landmarks=400, distance_matrix=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "coords = cpc.get_coordinates(perc=0.9, proj_dim=1)\n",
    "coords_R3 = ProjectiveMapUtils.hopf_map(coords)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next is the original pointcloud colored by the $z$-coordinate of the sphere coordinates obstained with complex projective coordinates."

   "source": [
    "%matplotlib widget\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8,4))\n",
    "ax = fig.add_subplot(projection=\"3d\")\n",
    "Y = X[pointcloud_permutation]\n",
    "ax.scatter(Y[:,0], Y[:,1], Y[:,2], s=5, c=coords_R3[:,2])\n",
    "PlotUtils.set_axes_equal(ax) ; plt.axis(\"off\") ; fig.subplots_adjust(top=1, bottom=0, left=0, right=1)"
   ]
